imdb.title: Purinsesu Chuchu
imdb.plot: A duck turned girl with magical powers must help save a prince from an unfinished fairy tale.

episodes.title: Ahiruto ôji sama
episodes.plot: Turned into a girl, all she wants to do is put a smile on Mytho's face. However, Duck will have one big ride with doing that.

episodes.title: Kokoro nokakera
episodes.plot: The Raven attacks Mytho. Duck tries to help, but she's helpless. Fakir seems only capable of writing what is happening. Mytho resolves to shatter his heart once more.

episodes.title: Purinsesu no chikai
episodes.plot: Princess Tutu is helping another person with their emotions. Ebine, a lonely cook, keeps people in their restuarant since her husband died. Though their doesn't seems to be much connection with some pairs.

episodes.title: Giselle
episodes.plot: A lonely ghost with unrequited love is towering through town. But for what purpose? We know our ballet hero is going to find out.

episodes.title: Himatsuri rino yoru ni
episodes.plot: Mytho gets locked in the closet by Fakir. After of course dancing with Duck and wanting to go with Rue to the Fire Festival. But something is keeping back Mytho in the place he's locked up in.

episodes.title: Yumemi ru orora
episodes.plot: Princess Tutu is having a battle with one of Mytho's heart shards. What is this heart shard though?

episodes.title: Karasu hime
episodes.plot: Things do not seem to be going well for Mytho now that the crow blood is rapidly taking him over. He now does the most idiotic thing by jumping out a window.

episodes.title: Senshi no izumi
episodes.plot: Rue, who has changed into Princess Kraehe, knocks down Duck when she talks with Mytho. But what's she doing there? What is Duck's purpose?

episodes.title: Kuroi kutsu
episodes.plot: Rue and Duck are starting to become good friends. But a battle takes place between Tutu and Kraehe, Tutu is far too weak to go into a battle with Kraehe, so therefore Kraehe as a crow disappears, with a very disappointed Fakir.

episodes.title: Shinderera
episodes.plot: After losing her necklace, Duck is stuck as a duck until she can get her necklace back. While she's a duck she will notice a different side of Fakir than she had before.

episodes.title: La Sylphide
episodes.plot: Mytho wants to give a gift to Princess Tutu, after hearing that giving a gift to someone shows how you feel about that person. But the necklace he's giving her might not have been a very good idea.

episodes.title: Yami no utage
episodes.plot: Rue reveals her part in the story. Duck learns that Mythos's feelings for Tutu might affect the outcome of the story.

episodes.title: Hakuchô no mizûmi
episodes.plot: A heartless Mythos is about to destroy his heart shard. But is she doing the right thing?

episodes.title: Dai karasu
episodes.plot: Unknown to Tutu, Fakir, and Mytho, Princess Kraehe put crow's blood into Mytho's heart shard of love, that will turn him into a person who loves crows and will marry only Princess Krakhe.

episodes.title: Coppelia
episodes.plot: Things do not seem to be going well for Mytho now that the crow blood is rapidly taking him over. He now does the most idiotic thing by jumping out a window.

episodes.title: Otome no inori
episodes.plot: Mytho tries to tell Mr. Cat that Fakir didn't push him out the window; but of course no one believes it. So Fakir and Duck try to wonder what happened to Mytho.

episodes.title: Tsumi to batsu
episodes.plot: Femio and his wholehearted views on love prompt Mytho to make the mime motion for love. This struggle with his evil self puts Mytho in the nurse's office.

episodes.title: Hôkô eru kishi
episodes.plot: After the drama club asks Fakir to perform in the story of the Phantom Knight, he begins to dream about him.

episodes.title: Manatsu no yoru no yume
episodes.plot: Duck learns that she's gathered all the heart shards that are hidden in people and now the only ones left are the ones sealing the Raven away.

episodes.title: Wasure rareta monogatari
episodes.plot: Duck meets a girl name Rachel, who is possibly a sister figure to Fakir. Rachel tells Duck that Fakir used to write stories that eventually came true.

episodes.title: Tsumugu mono tachi
episodes.plot: Fakir finds that Aotoa left a book for him. Fakir tracks him down and learns he is a direct descendent of Drosselmeyer. Fakir is tested to see if he truly has the power.

episodes.title: Ishi no kan
episodes.plot: Duck sets out in search of the rest of the heart shards, but becomes trapped in Drosselmeyer's world. Aotoa is jealous that Fakir is the chosen one.

episodes.title: Marionette
episodes.plot: Fakir sits down to write the order in which to save everyone from Drosselmeyer's clutches. Tutu is at Drosselmeyer's mercy in the world of gears. Kraehe begins to doubt whether Mytho will truly be hers and contemplates shattering his heart once again.

episodes.title: Ôji to karasu
episodes.plot: Fakir questions why he was able to write Duck's story, but not the one to save Mytho. Duck tries to get Rue to help her find the rest of the shards.

episodes.title: Hinshi no hakuchô
episodes.plot: The Raven consumes Rue, but she is still alive inside him. Mytho asks Tutu to restore the final piece of his heart so that he can go save her.

episodes.title: Finâre
episodes.plot: The Raven attacks Mytho. Duck tries to help, but she's helpless. Fakir seems only capable of writing what is happening. Mytho resolves to shatter his heart once more.
